    <h1>Russian Blue</h1>
    <img class="breed-photo" src="<%= ResolveUrl("~/html1/Pics/breeds/russian-blue.jpg") %>" alt="Russian Blue cat" />
    <p>The Russian Blue is a striking and sophisticated cat breed, celebrated for its shimmering silver-blue coat, vivid green eyes, and graceful, intelligent demeanor. Originating from Russia, this breed is believed to have been favored by Russian czars and nobility before spreading to Western Europe in the 19th century. The Russian Blue’s most recognizable feature is its short, dense double coat — a unique texture that feels like fine velvet. The coat’s blue-gray hue, tipped with silver, gives the cat a radiant, almost luminous appearance that glows in the light. Their elegant body is slender yet strong, with long legs, a fine-boned structure, and a slightly upturned mouth that gives them a subtle, perpetual “smile.” Their eyes are a brilliant emerald green, large and almond-shaped, perfectly complementing their cool, silvery coloring and adding to their mysterious, regal charm.

Personality-wise, the Russian Blue is known for being gentle, intelligent, and deeply loyal to its family. They tend to form strong bonds with their chosen person and often follow them quietly from room to room, showing affection through closeness rather than constant attention-seeking. While affectionate and loving once they trust you, they are typically shy around strangers and prefer calm, predictable environments. Russian Blues are highly intelligent and observant, quickly learning household routines and even simple commands. They are also known for their neatness — many owners note their fastidious grooming habits and preference for a clean litter box. Although they enjoy interactive play, especially with puzzle toys or feather wands, they are not hyperactive; their playfulness is balanced by a serene, almost aristocratic composure. Their soft, musical voices are used sparingly, often to communicate in gentle chirps or quiet meows.

Overall, the Russian Blue is a breed that embodies grace, refinement, and quiet devotion. With their enchanting looks, gentle nature, and loyal hearts, they make wonderful companions for those who appreciate a calm, intelligent, and affectionate feline presence in their lives.
 </p>
